    "body": "### Problem\n\nI am running i3 and using xterm. Under circumstances as in the attached video, when a new window is opened under the terminal that neovim is in, resizing the window, neovim segfaults. I tested this on both a packaged v0.7.2 from Debian, and on v0.10.0-dev-698+g02d859a07 built from source, and it happened on both. The attached ASAN log is from the second one.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/7697693/8f3cacdd-35f9-4124-959e-8d64a15f08d1\r\n\r\n[nvim_asan.53649.txt](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/files/12134979/nvim_asan.53649.txt)\r\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. nvim --clean\r\n2. insert text as in the video\r\n3. open a new window that resizes xterm\r\nThe amount of text seems to matter, so depending on your resolution and terminal font you may need a different amount of text.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nneovim doesn't segfault :)\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\ntested v0.7.2 and v0.10.0-dev-698+g02d859a07, happens on both\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, vim 9.0.1672\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nDebian sid\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nxterm 384\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nv0.7.2 from apt on Debian sid, v0.10.0-dev-698+g02d859a07 built from the repository",
    "closed_at": "2023-07-21T23:11:45Z",
